{"lemma": "فِتْنَةٌ", "slug": "فِتْنَةٌ", "root": "ف.ت.ن", "root_slug": "ف-ت-ن", "root_link": "/words/roots/ف-ت-ن", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "فِتْنَة", "root": "فتن", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 34}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 9}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n32971"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%AA%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "trial", "fa": "آزمایش", "ur": "فتنہ", "tr": "fitne", "id": "cobaan", "bn": "ফিতনা", "es": "prueba", "fr": "épreuve", "de": "Prüfung", "ru": "испытание", "zh": "考验"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "trial"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "strife"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "civil war"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sedition"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "tribulation"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "charm"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "craze"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "crime"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "huisache, Vachellia farnesiana", "tags": ["singulative"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Related with seduction and revolt. Compare فَتَنَ (fatana, “to trial”)."}, "ipa": ["/fit.na/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n32971", "headword_ar": "فِتْنَةٌ", "root": "ftn", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A burning with fire."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T.) ―         -b2-  And The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "melting"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of gold and of silver (K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in order to separate,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "distinguish, the bad from the good."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b3-  And [hence, or] from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fatana", "text_ar": "فَتَنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying “ he melted, ” (T,) or from that verb as signifying “ he put into the fire, “ (Msb,) gold, and silver, “ for that purpose, ” (T, Msb,) it signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A trial,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "probation;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, T, S, M, K, TA;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affliction, distress,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hardship;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) and [particularly]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an affliction whereby one is tried, proved,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tested:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, T, S, K, TA:) this is the sum of its meaning in the language of the Arabs: (T, TA: *) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "trial whereby the condition of a man may be evinced:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "this, accord. to Zj, may be the meaning in the Kur v. 45: (M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a mean whereby the condition of a man is evinced, in respect of good"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of evil:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Kull:) [hence it often means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a temptation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafotuwnN", "text_ar": "مَفْتُونٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapN", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, K,) meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a trial:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapN", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitanN", "text_ar": "فِتَنٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Msb.) It proceeds from God and from man: (Er-Rághib, TA:) [there are many instances of its proceeding from God in the Kur; for ex., in xxxvii. 61,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~aA", "text_ar": "اـِنَّا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaEalonaAhaA fitonapF lilZ~aAlimiyna", "text_ar": "جَعَلْنَاهَا فِتْنَةً لِلظَّالِمِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily we have made it to be"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a trial"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the wrongdoers"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is said in relation to the tree Ez-Zakkoom; the existence of which they disbelieved; for when they heard that it comes forth in the bottom of Hell, they said, Trees become burned in the fire; then how can they grow therein? (M.) [And hence] it signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Punishment, castigation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "chastisement."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, K.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Slaughter:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "civil war,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "conflict occurring among people:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "slaughter, and war, and faction,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sedition, among the parties of the Muslims when they form themselves into parties:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "discord, dissension,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "difference of opinions, among the people."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IAar, T, K.)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A misleading;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "causing to err,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "go astray:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K:) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seduction;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "temptation:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cause thereof; such as"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ornature, finery, show,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pomp,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "desires,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lusts, of the present life"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "world, whereby one is tried:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wealth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "children;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K, TA;) because one is tried thereby: (TA:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "women;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "than whom, the Prophet said, there is no"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonap", "text_ar": "فِتْنَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "more harmful to men: (T:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a cause of"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "one's"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "being pleased"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with a thing; (T, M, K;) as in the saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA tajoEalonaA fitonapF liloqawomi A@lZ~aAlimiyna", "text_ar": "لَا تَجْعَلْنَا فِتْنَةً لِلْقَوْمِ ا@لظَّالِمِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the Kur x. 85, i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Make not us to be a cause of pleasure"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2336}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the wrongdoing people"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; meaning, make not them to prevail over us, so as to become pleased with their unbelief and to think that they are better than we. (T.) Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Madness, insanity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diabolical possession;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "futuwnN", "text_ar": "فُتُونٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mafotuwnN", "text_ar": "مَفْتُونٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Error;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "deviation from the right way."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Infidelity;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unbelief:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, M, K:) thus in the saying, [in the Kur ii. 187,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waA@lofitonapu A^a$ad~u mina A@loqatoli", "text_ar": "وَا@لْفِتْنَةُ اَشَدُّ مِنَ ا@لْقَتْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And infidelity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "unbelief, is more excessive than slaughter:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the like is said in ii. 214]. (T.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A sin, a crime;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "an act of disobedience for which one deserves punishment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Disgrace, shame,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ignominy."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapu", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlS~adori", "text_ar": "الصَّدْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlwasowaAsu", "text_ar": "الوَسْوَاسُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The devil's prompting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "suggesting, of some evil idea"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapu AlmaHoyaA", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةُ المَحْيَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The being turned from the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "right"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "road:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapu AlmamaAti", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةُ المَمَاتِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The being questioned in the grave"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[by the two angels Munkar and Nekeer]:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitonapu AlD~ur~i", "text_ar": "فِتْنَةُ الضُّرِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sword:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fitotapu Als~ur~i", "text_ar": "فِتْتَةُ السُّرِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Women."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) [And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfitonapu AlEamoyaA", "text_ar": "الفِتْنَةُ العَمْيَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a phrase used in the present day as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Incurable evil"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "trouble."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]       -A2-  [It is also the name now commonly given to The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mimosa farnesiana"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of Linn.; (Delile's Floræ Ægypt. Illustr. no. 962;) called by Forskål (Flora Ægypt. Arab. p. lxxvii.)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mimosa scorpioïdes."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA", "T", "Msb", "IAar", "S", "M", "Kull"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}